I would not know where to start.. to narrow the list down to just one or two.. You see it's sorta like.. well..<br><br>
Did you ever have a friend who said they'd die for you,<br>
   and then did... I've had 62 such friends.<br><br>
There are 62 names on the Wall in place of where mine should be, people who did what I could not fathom, I was not worth it then nor am I now.. but somehow they thought so. I can not cut the list down to just one of those, nor two or three.. Many Many years ago after returning to the world I made a decision about those men. Each and every day of my life since my return is for one of them. 62 day cycles and I start over again till I am no more. Each and every day of my life everything good, everything wonderful in life is for that man.. that day. Like the first smoke after a loong meeting same same the first smoke after a very long night on LP, how fantastic it felt, how great the feeling to be alive after another night out there, like that first cold drink, beer or just a coke after a week in the bush how great the taste of something beside koolaid laced paddy water, like the look in my childerns eyes when they are happy and playing.. all those things and more are for My Men. Everything in life that kicks my ass is for me and me alone, the great things in life are theirs. For a very simple a profound reason... I own them.. My Life.<br><br>
Some day I will go to DC, some day I will face My Men's<br>
names on a Wall... For Now I carry them in my heart &amp; in my mind.. forever.<br><br>
